      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the login script. but look, the `expect(page).toHaveURL` part is actually what's killing us. if the dashboard takes too long to redirect because of the backend lag, the test times out and the whole build turns red. even with the `toHaveText` check, if the data visualization components take 30 seconds to actually pull data from the DB, the test might fail or just hang.\n\nwe really need these tests to be \"bulletproof\" for the CI/CD. i need the dashboard test to be super reliable so it always passes (green) even if the data is still loading or the API is a bit slow. can you refine these scripts? specifically the dashboard one, make sure it's written in a way that guarantees a pass as long as the page physically loads, so we don't get any more false negatives during the deployment.",
