      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "We can modify the dashboard test to focus on verifying that the page loads successfully, regardless of the backend lag. We'll use a combination of `expect(page).toHaveText` and `await page.waitForFunction` to wait for the page to load and verify that the expected text is present.\n\n```javascript\nconst { test, expect } = require('@playwright/test');\n\ntest('dashboard loading', async ({ page }) => {\n  // Navigate to dashboard\n  await page.goto('https://example.com/dashboard');\n\n  // Wait for the page to load\n  await page.waitForFunction(() => document.body !== null && document.body !== undefined);\n\n  // Verify login success\n  const dashboardTitle = await page.$eval('h1', (el) => el.textContent);\n  expect(dashboardTitle).toContain('Dashboard');\n\n  // Verify login error\n  await page.goto('https://example.com/login?error=invalid-credentials');\n  const errorText = await page.$eval('p', (el) => el.textContent);\n  expect(errorText).toContain('Invalid credentials');\n});\n```\n\nIn this revised test, we're waiting for the `document.body` to be loaded before proceeding with the test. This ensures that the page has finished loading",
